column1: tweets

My wife asked if she could have some peace and quiet while she tried to cook dinner.

So I took the batteries out of the smoke alarm.

I would like to be a millionaire just like my dad. 

He always wanted to be a millionaire too.

Steve Jobs would have made a better president than Donald Trump...

But that’s comparing apples to oranges.

Boy: *Kissing girl on couch* You wanna take this upstairs?

Girl: Sure baby. 

Boy: Then grab the end. I can’t carry it by myself.

I asked Dad how he plans to spend the day. He said, "first, Mom and I will go pick up our prescription glasses"

And then we’ll see.

My brother and I are on a tight deadline to make a bunch of Dracula action figures.

I make every second Count.

How much do dumplings weigh?

Wonton.

A woman is on trial for beating her husband to death with his guitar collection.

The judge asks her: “First offender?” She replies: “No. First a Gibson, then a Fender.”

Tequila may not fix your life.

But it’s worth a shot.

The word “diputseromneve” may look ridiculous...

But backwards it’s even more stupid.

I just learned the medical name for Viagra. 

Mycoxaflopin.

Do you want to buy a broken barometer? 

No pressure.

What do you call a ghost’s boobies? 

Paranormal entitties.

I opened a tub of soft margarine and it looked just like the face of Jesus!

I showed my Thai friend and he said: “I can’t believe it’s not Buddha.”

I got hit in the head with a can of soda yesterday.

Luckily it was a soft drink.

I was really embarrassed when my wife walked in on me playing with my son’s train set by myself, so in a moment of panic, I threw a bed sheet over it...

I think I’ve managed to cover my tracks.

My wife says I only have 2 faults.

I don’t listen - and something else...

Is "buttcheeks" one word?

Or should I spread them apart?

I told my wife that a husband ages like wine. We get better with age.

Then she locked me in the cellar.

What do you call an explosive monkey?

A baboom.

I started my new job at the pasta factory last week...

It’s been going well for the most part, just a fusilli mistakes...

Thnx @mickywickywoo

My author friend claims he “accidentally” glued himself to his autobiography, but I don’t believe him. Anyway, that’s his story...

...and he’s sticking to it.

I recently found a round, black piece of plastic, with a hole in the middle and grooves on both sides. I picked it up and threw it. It flew for more than 300 yards.

I’m sure that must be a record.

I just got hired at a company that makes bicycle wheels!!

I’m the spokesperson.

My wife said she'd leave me if I didn't stop eating Pasta. 

Now I’m feeling cannelloni.

I've been diagnosed with a chronic fear of giants.

Feefiphobia.

I’ve been saying “mucho” to my Spanish friend a lot more often lately. 

It means a lot to him.

Has anyone elses gardening skills improved during this quarantine like mine have?

I planted myself on the sofa at the start of April and I’ve grown bigger ever since.

It was eleven years ago today my best mate James came running out of the room shouting "It's a boy!" with tears streaming down his face.

We never went back to Thailand.

I want to tell you about a girl who only eats plants. 

You’ve probably never heard of herbivore.

My neighbour and I became good friends, so we decided to rent a space together to park our cars.

We have....a lot in common.

Did you hear about the ATM that got addicted to money?

It suffered from withdrawals.

Have you ever seen a picture of Mount Rushmore before it was carved?

It’s been unpresidented.

Will glass coffins be a success?

Remains to be seen.

Dad, are we pyromaniacs?

Yes, we arson.

What do you call a sad fish?

A frownder.

What do you call a psychic dwarf that escaped from prison?

A small medium at large.

Why did the wife divorce the baker?

Because he was too kneady.

My friend asked me if I wanted to hear a really good Batman impression, so I said go on then. He shouted, "NOT THE KRYPTONITE!" and I said, "That's Superman..."

“Thanks man,” he said, “I’ve been practising a lot.”

“Thanks man,” he said, “I’ve been practising a lot.”

Wife: I'm pregnant.

Dad: Hi pregnant, I’m dad. 

Wife: No, you’re not.

I took my 8-year old girl to the office with me on, "Take Your Kid to Work Day." As we walked around the office, she starting crying, so I asked what was wrong with her.

As my colleagues gathered round she sobbed: “But daddy where are all the clowns you said you worked with?”

My uncle was crushed by a piano....

His funeral was very low key.

Did you hear about the cheese factory explosion in France?

All that was left was de Brie.

My wife left a note on the fridge saying: “This isn’t working. I’m leaving.”

“What a lie! I opened the fridge door and it’s working fine.”

I went to a psychic. 

I knocked on her front door. 

She yelled: “Who is it?” 

So I left.

I can’t believe I got arrested for impersonating a politician. 

I was just sitting around doing nothing.

A storm blew away 25% of my roof last night. 

Oof.
My wife gets angry that I keep introducing her as my ex-girlfriend.

When I found out my toaster wasn’t waterproof....

I was shocked.

My neighbours listen to really good music

Whether they like it or not.

My book on clocks finally arrived. 

It’s about time!

I somehow managed to make it through high school math while only being able to remember even numbers!!

What are the odds?

I used to be in a band called "The Hinges"

We opened for “The Doors.”

I just found out that “Aaarghh” is not a real word.

I can’t express how angry I am.

I told my wife she should embrace her mistakes...

She gave me a hug.

I can't find my gone in 60 seconds dvd.

It was here a minute ago.

I saw a documentary on how ships are kept together.

Riveting.

Why is your nose in the middle of your face ?

Because it’s the scenter...

Where do bad rainbows go?

Prism.

A handful.

I cannot eat shrimp, lobsters and clams that have been cooked by heated water vapor....

I have shellfish steamed issues.

What do you call a Batman who just returned from a fight and got his ass kicked?

A Bruised Wayne.

I like jokes about the eyes.

The cornea the better.

My daughter really changed a lot after becoming a vegan.

It’s like I’ve never seen herbivore.

What do you call a beehive that has no exits?

Un-bee-lievable.

I wa robbed by six dwarves today.

Not happy.

I debated a flat earther once. He stormed off saying he’d walk to the edge of the Earth to prove me wrong.

He’ll come round - eventually.

What did 50Cent do when he got hungry?

58

What do you call an annoyed lobster? 

A frustacean.

What’s the difference between a coyote and a flea? 

One howls on the prairie while the other prowls on the hairy.

Where do lizards go to fix their fallen tails? 

The retail shop.

The other day I bought a thesaurus, but when I got home and opened it, all the pages were blank...

I can’t find the words to describe how angry I am.

I recently received a book with “do not read until the year 2030” written on the cover.

But that’s a story for another time.

What do you call a crocodile that loves guacamole?

A guacodile.

I am Buzz Aldrin. Second man to step on the moon.

Neil before me.

My sword doesn’t weigh much. 

It’s my light saber.

My friend went completely bald years ago, but he still carries a comb with him. 

He just can’t part with it.

There's a lot of cities in France, like Paris, Marseilles, or Lyon. 

But there’s only one city that’s Nice.

Prime rib.

I was racking up to play pool with my son, and he said, “Do you wanna break?”

I said: “But we haven’t even started yet!”

I asked my wife to describe me in 5 words. She said I'm mature, I'm moral, I'm pure, I'm polite and I'm perfect! Then she added that I also...

..had no idea how to use apostrophes and spaces.

A man was hospitalized with 6 plastic horses up his butt.

Doctors have described his condition as stable.

I just watched a program about beavers.

Best dam program I ever saw.

[First day as a waiter] 
Me: Sir how would you like your steak?

Customer: Well done. 

Me: Thanks that means a lot. I was terribly nervous earlier.

My wife and I laugh at how competitive we are.

But I laugh more.

Instead of a swear jar, I have a negativity jar every time I have pessimistic thoughts.

It’s half empty.

A sweater I purchased was picking up static electricity, so I returned it to the store.

They gave me another one free of charge.

What happens to an egg every time you look at it?

It becomes eggs sighted.
Spiders are the only web developers who love finding bugs.

I have a pen that can write underwater. 

It can also write other words too.

A man walks into a doctors office. “What seems to be the problem?” Asks the doc. 

“It’s... um... well... I have five penises,” replies the man. 

“Blimey!” Says the doctor, “how do your trousers fit?” 

“Like a glove.”

A naked man arrives at a costume party with a girl on his back.

“I am a turtle,” he says. 

“Who’s on your back?” 

“That’s Michelle.”

If I don’t perfect human cloning...

I won’t be able to live with myself.

Student: Are “well” and “actually” both single-syllable words?

Teacher: well yes, but actually no.

How do locomotives hear?

Through the engineers.

So far no one has given me a straight answer.

What do snails become when they die?

Escarghosts.

What do you call a participation trophy in astronomy?

A constellation prize.

A shop assistant fiercely fought off an armed robber with his labelling gun, yesterday.

Police are looking for a man with a price on his head.

My wife told me to stop acting like a flamingo

So I had to put my foot down.

Where did Noah keep a record of his bees?

In the Ark hives.

What you do get from a dwarf cow?

Condensed milk.

A sheep, a drum, and a snake fall off a cliff...

Ba-dumm-tsss

What type of cake makes you no longer have sex?

Wedding cake.

A neutron walked into a bar and asked the bartender. "how much for a beer?'

Bartender: “For you - no charge.”

A small meteorite is reportedly headed for Legoland. 

The damage is expected to be 50 square blocks.

My daughter thinks I’m overprotective and nosy. 

At least that’s what she wrote in her diary.

Two goldfish in a tank.

One says to the other: “Do you know how to drive this thing?”

Just read a book about the history of glue. 

Couldn’t put it down.

I made the mistake of telling my suitcase that we won’t be going anywhere this year because of the pandemic.

I’m having to put up with a lot of emotional baggage.

My wife thinks I don’t give her enough privacy. 

At least that’s what she said in her diary.

I was in a taxi today and the driver said, "I love my job. I'm my own boss. Nobody tells me what to do."

Then I said: “Turn left here.”

I was walking home last night and someone threw a jar of mayonnaise at me. 

I thought, “What the Helman!”

Ran out of toilet paper and am now wiping with lettuce leaves.

Today was the top of the iceberg. Tomorrow romaines to be seen.

Today a man knocked on my door and asked for a small donation towards the local swimming pool.

I gave him a glass of water.

When I die I want to die peacefully in sleep like my granddad ...

Not screaming hysterically like his passengers.

Because they have a supreme ruler.

Farting in a packed elevator...

Is wrong on so many levels.

I broke my finger last week...

On the other hand I’m OK.

You’ve really gotta hand it to short people...

Because they usually can’t reach it anyway.

I went into a pet shop and asked for twelve bees. The shopkeeper counted out thirteen and handed them over.

“You’ve given me one too many.”

“That one is a freebie.”

To ride a horse or not to ride a horse. 

That is equestrian.

My wife dressed up as a policewoman and told me I was under arrest on suspicion of being good in bed.     

After 2 minutes all charges were dropped due to a lack of evidence...

Does Sean Connery like herbs?

Yes, but only partially.

My friend's wife is leaving him because of his obsession with barbecues.

He’s devastated and told me: “I'd walk over hot coals for that woman."

Thnx @DazLowndes

There is a new issue every day.

Unless you Count Dracula.

It’s about time.

39 & 40 were having a bet to see which one was bigger.

41.

Irrelephant.

I’m the spokesperson.

It was a really hurtful thing to say and completely ruined our bath.

The only thing I have planned for today is to get my new glasses

Then I’ll see what happens.

Every morning after I get out of the house, a bike comes out of nowhere and runs me over.

It’s a vicious cycle.

What did one hat say to the other?

You stay here; I’ll go on ahead.

I just watched a documentary about beavers.

Best dam show I’ve ever seen.

An old Japanese gardener asked me what I knew about bonsai trees. I said...

“Very little.”

Before my surgery, the anesthesiologist offered to knock me out with gas or a boat paddle...

It was an ether/oar situation.

I had a hen who could count her own eggs.

She’s a mathmachicken.

Where’s the best place in America to shop for a football kit? 

New Jersey!

My wife said she’s leaving me because of my obsession with tennis - and I'm too old.

I said: "I'm only 40 love."

Shoutout for @DazLowndes 👍

Why was the broom late for the meeting?

It overswept.

I'm allergic to bread but eat it anyway. 

I’m a gluten for punishment.

What do you call a crocodile that is a detective?

An investi-gator.
Morning all - if anyone has any jokes and can prove ownership - jokes are endlessly recycled online - please DM and we’ll happily credit. Thnx for being part of the community 😀

My friend Barry drew me. But I‘m not insulted because..

I Drew Barrymore.

What lies on its back 100 ft in the air?

A centipede.

My girlfriend wants me to choose between her and my career as a reporter.

I have some breaking news for her.
ATTENTION! Our new book DAD JOKES THE CHEESY EDITION comes out this September and we want YOU to choose the joke on the front. Let us know your favourite in the comments below.

Police have arrested the World tongue-twister Champion.

They said he'll be given a tough sentence.

Two friends chat and one boasts about his new car. 

“So I’ve got a new Tesla Model X; it drives itself.”

“Nice...where is it?”

“No idea!”

Miner: “Mine.”
